Torneo Clausura (Chile)|2003]]\n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n\n|14||8||||||||||14||8\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!490||233||73||50||44||26||612||348<ref>{{cite news |title=El top 12 de los m\u00e1s grandes goleadores de Chile |url=https://mouse.latercera.com/el-top-12-de-los-mas-grandes-goleadores-de-chile/ |accessdate=11 April 2020 |work=La Tercera |date=8 May 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===International===\n:Source:<ref name=\"Iv\u00e1n Luis Zamorano \u2013 Goals in International Matches\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/zamorano-intlg.html\n| title = Iv\u00e1n Luis Zamorano \u2013 Goals in International Matches\n| publisher = Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation\n| accessdate = 17 October 2010 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|colspan=\"3\"|[[Chile national football team|Chile national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|-\n|1987||5||1\n|-\n|1988||5||0\n|-\n|1989||2||1\n|-\n|1990||0||0\n|-\n|1991||9||6\n|-\n|1992||0||0\n|-\n|1993||1||0\n|-\n|1994||2||2\n|-\n|1995||1||1\n|-\n|1996||8||5\n|-\n|1997||5||9\n|-\n|1998||8||2\n|-\n|1999||8||3\n|-\n|2000||10||4\n|-\n|2001||5||0\n|-\n!Total||69||34\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Chile's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"Iv\u00e1n Luis Zamorano \u2013 Goals in International Matches\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\n|-\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 19 June 1987 || [[Estadio Nacional (Lima)|Estadio Nacional]], [[Lima]] || {{fb|Peru}} || '''3'''\u20131 || 3\u20131 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 2. || 6 August 1989 || [[Br\u00edgido Iriarte Stadium]], [[Caracas]] || {{fb|Venezuela}} || '''3'''\u20131 || 3\u20131 ||  [[1990 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|1990 World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 3. || 30 June 1991 || [[Estadio Nacional de Chile]], [[Santiago]] || {{fb|Ecuador}} || '''2'''\u20130 || 3\u20131 || Friendly\n|-\n| 4. || 6 July 1991 || Estadio Nacional