arolina]]. The team competes in the [[NCAA Division II]] and are members of the [[South Atlantic Conference]]. Lenoir\u2013Rhyne's first football team was fielded in 1907. The team plays its home games at the 10,000 seat [[Moretz Stadium]] in [[Hickory, North Carolina]].\n\n==History==\n{{Expand section|date=October 2012}}\n\n==Conference history==\n*1954\u20131969: [[National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics|NAIA]]\n*1970\u20131992: NAIA Division I\n*1989\u2013present: NCAA Division II\n\n===Conference affiliations===\n*1907\u20131930: Independent\n*1931\u20131960: [[North State Conference]]\n*1961\u20131974: [[Carolinas Conference]]\n*1975\u2013present: [[South Atlantic Conference]]\nThe Bears had no team from 1912\u20131920 and 1942\u20131945.\n\n==Bowl games==\nThe Bears have participated in five postseason [[bowl games]], compiling a 3\u20132 record.<ref name=NCAApdf>{{cite web |url=http://fs.ncaa.org/Docs/stats/football_records/2016/bowls.pdf |title=BOWL/ALL STAR GAME RECORDS |year=2016 |publisher=NCAA |accessdate=January 7, 2017}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Season\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Game\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Date\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Opponent\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Result\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Location\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| 1951 || [[Pythian Bowl]] || December 8, 1951 || [[California Vulcans football|California (PA)]] || '''W''' 13\u20137 || [[Salisbury, North Carolina]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| 1952 || [[Cigar Bowl]] || December 13, 1952 || [[Tampa Spartans football|Tampa]] || L 12\u201321 || [[Tampa, Florida]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| 1955 || Palmetto Shrine || December 10, 1955 || [[Newberry Wolves|Newberry]] || '''W''' 14\u201313 || [[Columbia, South Carolina]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| 1959 || [[Holiday Bowl (NAIA)]