eward]], former wide receiver for the [[Dallas Cowboys]] (1987)\n\n==Year-by-year results==\n1939* (6\u20131\u20133), 1951 (10\u20131), 1952 (8\u20131), 1955 (9\u20130\u20131), 1956 (10\u20130), 1958 (9\u20131), 1959 (10\u20131), 1960 (12\u20130), 1961 (8\u20131\u20131), 1962 (11\u20131), 1965 (7\u20133), 1966* (6\u20133), 1967 (8\u20131), 1975 (7\u20133\u20131), 1988* (7\u20134), 1994* (8\u20132), 2005 (5\u20135), 2006 (3\u20138), 2007 (2\u20139), 2008 (3\u20138), 2009 (5\u20136), 2010 (7\u20134), 2011* (7\u20133), 2012 (9\u20133), 2013* (13\u20132), 2014* (11\u20131), 2015 (5\u20135), 2016 (3\u20138), 2017 (3\u20137), 2018* (12\u20132), 2019* (13\u20131)\n\n==Championship appearances==\nThe Bears made three appearances in the NAIA championship game during their tenure, winning in 1960, and appeared in the NCAA Division II championship game in 2013.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:60%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Year\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Division\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Coach\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Opponent\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Record\n!style=\"background:#AB002D; color:#FFFFFF;\" |Score\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| [[1959 Lenoir-Rhyne Bears football team|1959]] || [[1959 NAIA football season|NAIA Playoffs]] || [[Clarence Stasavich]] || [[Texas A&M\u2013Kingsville Javelinas football|Texas A&I Javelinas]] || 10\u20131 || L 20\u20137\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| [[1960 Lenoir-Rhyne Bears football team|1960]] || [[1960 NAIA football season|NAIA Playoffs]] || [[Clarence Stasavich]] || [[1960 Humboldt State Lumberjacks football team|Humboldt State]] || 12\u20130 || '''W''' 15\u201314\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| [[1962 Lenoir-Rhyne Bears football team|1962]] || [[1962 NAIA football season|NAIA Playoffs]] || [[Hanley Painter]] || [[1962 Central State Bronchos football|Central State (OK)]] || 11\u20131 || L 13\u201328